            Done. Here's what was created:

            ### Plugin Generator (`scripts/new-plugin.sh`)

            ```bash
            ./scripts/new-plugin.sh my-plugin tools       # Tools plugin
            ./scripts/new-plugin.sh my-plugin storage     # Storage plugin
            ./scripts/new-plugin.sh my-plugin transport   # Transport plugin
            ```

            Scaffolds a complete plugin with:
            - `cmd/main.go` (type-specific, matching existing plugin patterns)
            - `internal/` starter code (tools: plugin.go + tools/hello.go + storage/client.go, storage: storage.go + reader.go + writer.go, transport: transport.go + handler.go)
            - `go.mod`, `README.md`, `LICENSE`, `CHANGELOG.md`, `CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md`, `SECURITY.md`, `.gitignore`
            - `docs/` and `.github/` with CI + issue templates
            - Auto-updates `go.work`, `Makefile`, `sync-repos.sh`, `release.sh`
            - Runs `go mod tidy` and `git init`

            Tested: generated a tools plugin, verified it builds and vets clean, then cleaned up.

            ### Deployment-Ready Files

            | File | Status |
            |------|--------|
            | `SECURITY.md` | Created |
            | `CHANGELOG.md` | Updated (was placeholder, now proper Keep-a-Changelog format) |
            | `CONTRIBUTING.md` | Created |

            All 5 binaries build, all 62 tests pass.
